<section xml:id="sec-limit-laws" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Limit Laws</title>

  <paragraphs>
    <title>Module Learning Objectives</title>
  
    <ol>
      <li>State the various Limit Laws</li>
      <li>Apply Limit Laws, when appropriate, to quickly compute limits (ex: rational functions when denominator is nonzero)</li>
      <li>Apply the Squeeze Theorem (aka Sandwich Theorem) to compute limits</li>
      <li>Apply algebraic techniques to compute limits</li>
    </ol>
  </paragraphs>



